               <head>Yazdi's Zafarnamah, early and later copies in one</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Ẓafar'nāmah by Sharaf al-Dīn ʻAlī Yazdī, -1454</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85135483 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/no2007011345 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91005420" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4634-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659027.0x000001 viaf_95224252">Sharaf al-Dīn ʻAlī Yazdī, -1454</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164659027.0x000001 viaf_95224252">شرف الدين على يزدى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20110">Ẓafar'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20110">ظفر نامه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>The celebrated history of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_63984707" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50015000" role="subject">Amīr Taymūr</persName> (771-807/1370-1404) and Khalīl Sulṭān (807-814/1404-1411), completed first by Ibrāhīm Sulṭan, and then elaborated into his final form by Yazdī, and completed 828/1424-5. This copy was transcribed only four years after the author’s death 
                        </p>
                        <p>It is preceded by the iftitāḥ or muqaddimah, a genealogical account of the Turkish Khāns with a history of Chingīz Khān and his successors by Sharaf al-Dīn in 822/1419 </p>
                        <p>Consists of 2 parts of differing dates: Part I (ff. 1-76), dated Burhānpūr, 12 Rabīʿ II 1023/22 May 1614; Part II (ff. 77-405), dated 7 Rabīʿ II 862/22 February 1458 </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
